BY JUDITE CYPRESTE

Since ancient times, humans have had curiosity about understanding their own bodies. The curiosity to comprehend how and what we are made of led artists to purchase or steal cadavers in search of answers. Although science has evolved enough to provide more effective methods to satisfy our curiosity, humans still revere and strive to understand their own bodies.

To contribute to this quest, I attempted to understand how humans talk about their own bodies in one of the most important and respected sources of effective answers about humanity today: Spotify songs.

Armpits, knees, and necks: how do the platform's most popular songs sing about our bodies? What do these songs celebrate (or not) about our bodies? What is the human relationship with oneself?

Below, you will find a selection of body parts and excerpts from songs that mention them. You also have the chance to listen to the song if you are curious or simply don't want to miss anything.

WARNING: Some songs may contain explicit or offensive language. Learn more about the methodology at the end of this page.

The collection of songs on the Spotify platform and subsequent analysis were conducted using the Python programming language.

For the data collection part, the ten most popular songs on the platform were searched, using the body part to be investigated as the keyword.

In order of popularity, they were listened to and read for validation. Later, they were selected and grouped in the playlist below, which you can listen to if you enjoyed this analysis. The entire code and data are available here.
